---

<section class="py-24 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-100 text-center mb-16">
      Generic AI is worse than no AI.
    </h2>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-16">

      <!-- P1 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative">
          <div class="text-amber-400/30 font-display font-bold text-6xl absolute top-4 right-5 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none">01</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-2xl mb-4 relative z-10">01</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">
            <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-100">"It doesn't know your clients."</span><br />
            You explain your context every session. Your projects, your clients, your voice — gone. The AI helps everyone the same way, because it doesn't know you.
          </p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-700 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"Claude remembers convos. NotebookLM knows my uploads. My actual brain lives somewhere else entirely."</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- P2 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative">
          <div class="text-amber-400/30 font-display font-bold text-6xl absolute top-4 right-5 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none">02</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-2xl mb-4 relative z-10">02</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">You tried building a system yourself. It took a weekend, worked for two weeks, then fell apart when your projects changed.</p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-700 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"I'm trying to build an AI Second Brain and I'm losing mine doing it."</p>
          <cite class="text-zinc-600 text-xs not-italic mt-1 block">— r/Obsidian</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- P3 -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
        <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 relative">
          <div class="text-amber-400/30 font-display font-bold text-6xl absolute top-4 right-5 leading-none select-none pointer-events-none">03</div>
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-display font-bold text-2xl mb-4 relative z-10">03</div>
          <p class="text-zinc-300 text-base leading-relaxed relative z-10">Every session starts from zero. Your AI has no memory of what you built last month, who you talked to, or what you decided.</p>
        </div>
        <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-zinc-700 pl-3">
          <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm italic leading-relaxed">"It's a goldfish."</p>
          <cite class="text-zinc-600 text-xs not-italic mt-1 block">— Developer on GitHub</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-zinc-400 text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      AI systems decay without maintenance.
      <span class="text-zinc-100 font-medium"> BrainKit is your maintenance contract.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
